<HEADLINE> Court Upholds Rosanne, Arnold Suit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- A federal appeals court has upheld the  
$750,000 damage award given to Roseanne and ex-husband Tom Arnold 
in a dispute with a clothing manufacturer. 
</P>
<P>
	In a 3-0 ruling Thursday, the 9th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals  
said the couple had a binding contract with Celeb Sales, which 
promised them $1 million in November 1993 but paid only $250,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Celeb Sales planned to market ``Roseanne'' and ``Tom'' lines of  
clothing for larger people. The company claimed the Arnolds 
undermined the deal by generating bad publicity. 
</P>
<P>
	After the pair sued the company, Celeb Sales countersued for $24  
million, contending the couple reneged on an agreement to market 
the clothing on cable television. 
</P>
<P>
	U.S. District Judge Harry Hupp dismissed the company's fraud  
claim, and a jury found that Celeb Sales had violated its contract. 
</P>
