<DOCNO> APW19990318.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-18 12:33:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Push Ahead; Dow Up 67.15 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow industrials moved back toward 10,000  
today as stock prices rose in response to another positive report 
on inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	At 3 p.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
up 67.15 to 9,946.56. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were higher as well, with the Standard  
&AMP; Poor's 500 index up 15.19 at 1,313.01, and the technology-heavy 
Nasdaq composite index up 25.61 at 2,454.58. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow briefly crossed 10,000 on Tuesday, but the blue-chip  
index quickly backed off, closed lower and then added to its losses 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The immediate cause of today's advance was a Labor Department  
report this morning that consumer prices rose a tiny 0.1 percent 
last month. That was a confirmation that inflation remains in check 
and a signal that the Federal Reserve is unlikely to raise 
short-term interest rates anytime soon. 
</P>
<P>
	The consumer price report boosted prices in the bond market,  
where the 30-year Treasury bond was up 3/8 point and its yield, which 
moves opposite from its price, fell to 5.47 percent from 5.5 
percent late Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors were unfazed by a separate report from the Commerce  
Department that the nation's trade deficit shot up 21 percent in 
January. 
</P>
<P>
	They were also undisturbed by the continuing rise in oil prices,  
which longer-term could prove inflationary. ``Oil is turning the 
corner,'' said Gregory Nie, a technical analyst at Everen 
Securities in Chicago, ``but there will be a proving period over 
the short term where you get a correction in crude that will take a 
little starch out of this move up.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Today, higher oil prices fed advances in oil stocks. Dow member  
Exxon was up 5/8 at 74 15/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Dow components were also led higher by financial services  
stocks, which reacted positively to a report that Chase Manhattan 
Corp. is looking for a merger partner. Chase shares were up 1 13/16 
at 84 3/16. American Express was leading the Dow components higher 
and was up 5 1/16 at 126. 
</P>
<P>
	Traders also said Friday's triple expiration of options and  
futures contracts lent a slightly positive bias to stock prices 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues were barely edging out decliners on the New  
York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 675.87 million shares, up 
from Wednesday's pace. 


</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
