<HEADLINE> Boxer Whitaker Pleads Guilty to DUI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. (AP) -- Former world boxing champion and  
Olympic gold medalist Pernell ``Sweetpea'' Whitaker pleaded guilty 
to driving under the influence of alcohol. 
</P>
<P>
	Whitaker was fined $1,000 and his driver's license was suspended  
for a year during a hearing into the June 4 incident Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	General District Judge Robert L. Simpson also imposed a 60-day  
jail sentence that was suspended on the condition that Whitaker 
stay out of trouble. He ordered Whitaker to attend an alcohol 
safety education program. 
</P>
<P>
	Whitaker declined to comment after the hearing.  
</P>
<P>
	The 35-year-old Whitaker has been undisputed lightweight  
champion and has held pieces of the junior welterweight, 
welterweight and junior middleweight titles. He suffered the third 
loss of his pro career last month to Felix Trinidad. 
</P>
<P>
	He was suspended from boxing for seven months after he tested  
positive for cocaine and was reinstated Sept. 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
