<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Ski Jumper Survives Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PLANICA, Slovenia (AP) -- Ski jumper Valery Kobelev of Russia  
suffered a concussion and severe neck bruises in a terrifying crash 
during qualifying Thursday for a ski flying World Cup competition. 
</P>
<P>
	Kobelev, 25, was taken by helicopter to the intensive care unit  
of a hospital in Ljubljana, the Slovenian capital. 
</P>
<P>
	He was sedated and on a respirator, but a computer scan revealed  
no brain, head or spine injuries, a hospital statement said. 
</P>
<P>
	Kobelev was swept by a gust of wind, lost control in the air and  
crashed head-first into the landing area of the mammoth ski flying 
hill in this Slovenian resort. After tumbling down the hill, he was 
taken away in a stretcher unconscious. 
</P>
<P>
	The qualifying session for the final World Cup event of the  
season was delayed and often interrupted by gusts of wind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
