<HEADLINE> AP Top News at 4 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Dow 10,000 Down to the Wire  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average hit the 10,000  
mark again just before the close today, then started to fall. The 
Dow briefly hit 10,000 on Tuesday, but has never closed at that 
level. Just before the 4 p.m. EST close, the Dow was up around 110 
points at the 9,990 level. New York Stock Exchange advancers led 
decliners 1,509-1,377. The Nasdaq Composite Index was up 27.70 at 
2,456.67. 

</P>
<P>
	Tobacco Industry Wins Case in Ohio  
</P>
<P>
	AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- A federal jury handed the tobacco industry a  
