<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A gusty cold front barreled toward the Northeast today, while  
rain and snow struck the Southwest and southern Plains. Still 
another front soaked the Northwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Up to 8 inches of snow were possible by tonight in the mountains  
of Arizona and New Mexico, accompanied by blustery winds. Strong 
thunderstorms and rain were forecast in Texas and Oklahoma. 
</P>
<P>
	Six inches of snow were possible in the Northwest mountains  
today, with rain likely in Oregon and northern California. Light 
snow was also possible in the Great Lakes and New England today, 
while the rest of the Northeast was expected to see winds up to 35 
mph. 
</P>
<P>
	Calm and mild conditions were forecast for the Southeast,  
Midwest and West today. 
</P>
<P>
	The highest temperature in the continental United States on  
Wednesday was 78 degrees at Kingsville, Texas. The low was minus-4 
at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo. 
</P>
<P>
	Highs today were forecast to reach the 30s and 40s in northern  
New England, the Great Lakes and Plains; the 50s and 60s in the 
Northeast, Midwest, Rockies and West; and the 70s and 80s in the 
Southeast and Southwest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
