<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Virginia Fire Kills Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) -- Four bodies were found Thursday in an  
abandoned building that burned to the ground in an area frequented 
by homeless people. 
</P>
<P>
	The two-story wooden building that investigators said might have  
been a house or a storage shed was in a heavily wooded ravine and 
posted with ``No Trespassing'' signs. It was three miles from 
George Washington's estate. 
</P>
<P>
	The four adults were burned beyond recognition. Investigators  
said they were unable to determine their sex and didn't know 
whether they were homeless people taking refuge in the building. 
Autopsies were scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of the fire was under investigation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
