<HEADLINE> Clippers Activate Sherman Douglas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Los Angeles Clippers activated guard  
Sherman Douglas from the injured list on Thursday and made room for 
him on the roster by waiving guard James Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
	Douglas, on the injured list due to a sprained left groin since  
March 10, has averaged 5.7 points, 3.0 assists and 22.0 minutes in 
15 games for the Clippers. 
</P>
<P>
	Douglas, 32, signed with the Clippers as a free agent on Feb. 4.  
He will be in uniform Friday night when the team plays at Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson, 28, averaged 7.6 points and 1.9 rebounds in 14 games  
this season. He joined the Clippers as a free agent prior to last 
season, when he averaged 7.7 points in 70 games. 
</P>
