<HEADLINE> Bonds Rise in Light Trading / Bonds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Bond prices rose slightly in quiet trading  
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The price of the benchmark 30-year Treasury bond rose 9/32  
point, or $2.81 per $1,000 in face value. Its yield, which moves in 
the opposite direction, fell to 5.49 percent from 5.50 percent late 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In the broader market, prices of short-term Treasury securities  
were up 1/32 point, and intermediate maturities were up 1/8 point to 
3/16 point, reported Bridge Telerate, a financial information 
service. 
</P>
<P>
	The Lehman Brothers Daily Treasury Bond Index, reflecting price  
movements on bonds with maturities of a year or longer, fell 0.48 
point to 1,290.22 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields on three-month Treasury bills were 4.49 percent as the  
discount fell 0.02 percentage point to 4.38 percent. Six-month 
yields were 4.62 percent, as the discount fell 0.02 percentage 
point to 4.45 percent. One-year yields were 4.69 percent as the 
discount fell by 0.02 percentage point from late Wednesday to 4.47 
percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Yields are the interest bonds pay by maturity, while the  
discount is the interest at which they are sold. 
</P>
<P>
	The federal funds rate, the interest on overnight loans between  
banks, was unchanged from late Wednesday at 4.75 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In the tax-exempt market, the Bond Buyer index of 40 actively  
traded municipal bonds rose to 125 1/4 from 124 21/32. The average 
yield to maturity fell to 5.17 percent from 5.18 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
