<HEADLINE> AT&AMP;T Announces 3-for-2 Stock Split </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- AT&AMP;T Corp. is splitting its stock 3-for-2, an  
announcement that sent the nation's most widely held stock rising 
nearly 2 percent Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The stock split, which takes effect April 15, will give AT&AMP;T  
shareholders three shares of stock for every two they hold now. 
Shareholders as of the close of business March 31 are eligible. 
</P>
<P>
	AT&AMP;T, the nation's largest phone company, also announced that  
John Malone was elected to its board of directors. Malone headed 
Tele-Communications Inc., the huge cable TV company AT&AMP;T has 
acquired. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street welcomed the news of the stock split, sending AT&AMP;T  
shares up $1.56 1/4 to close at $84 a share on the New York Stock 
Exchange. 

</P>
</TEXT>
