<HEADLINE> Federated Completes Fingerhut Buy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Federated Department Stores Inc. said Thursday  
it has completed a $1.7 billion purchase of Fingerhut Cos. Inc., 
strengthening the retailer's ability to reach shoppers through 
catalogs and the Internet. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cincinnati-based parent company of such retail chains as  
Bloomingdale's and Macy's is paying $300 million in cash and 
assuming $1.4 billion in debt in the deal, Federated spokeswoman 
Carol Sanger said. 
</P>
<P>
	Federated is looking to benefit from Fingerhut's expertise in  
handling orders through catalogs and the Internet, in addition to 
database management and direct marketing. 
</P>
<P>
	Federated already operates the direct-mail catalogs  
Bloomingdale's By Mail and a Macys.com Web site. 
</P>
<P>
	A year ago, Dayton Hudson Corp., another large department store  
chain, purchased direct-seller Rivertown Trading Co. 
</P>
<P>
	Fingerhut's core catalog generates most of the company's roughly  
$2 billion in annual sales. It also has a food and gift catalog 
called Figi's; the apparel catalogs named Arizona Mail Order and 
Bedford Fair; and a membership-based general merchandise catalog 
named Popular Club. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to its own Web sites, Fingerhut has minority  
interests in four electronic-commerce companies: PC Flowers &AMP; 
Gifts; FreeShop.com; The Zone Network, parent of mountainzone.com; 
and Roxy Systems, an Internet marketer of digital communications 
and entertainment services. 
</P>
<P>
	Federated has annual sales of more than $15.8 billion. The  
retailer operates more than 400 department stores in 33 states 
under the names Bloomingdale's, The Bon Marche, Burdines, 
Goldsmith's, Lazarus, Macy's, Rich's and Stern's. 

</P>
</TEXT>
