<HEADLINE> Court To Rule on Stooges T-Shirts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- California's Supreme Court will soitenly  
decide whether Gary Saderup has the right to market Three Stooges 
T-shirts. 
</P>
<P>
	The high court agreed Wednesday to review a $75,000 verdict  
against Saderup for producing T-shirts with charcoal sketches of 
Larry, Moe and Curly. 
</P>
<P>
	Comedy III Productions, which holds the commercial rights to the  
Three Stooges, had sued Saderup and won under a California law that 
prohibits the unauthorized commercial use of a dead celebrity's 
likeness. 
</P>
<P>
	On appeal, Saderup argued that he is an artist whose work in  
protected by the Constitution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
