<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Dow Flirts With 10,000, Pulls Back  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average cracked 10,000  
six times today but pulled back each time, finishing a nail-biting 
session less than three points below the mark. The blue-chip index 
ended at 9,997.62, up 118.21 for a record high close. It was the 
second day that the Dow had crossed 10,000 but failed to hold its 
gains -- on Tuesday, the index briefly traded as high as 10,001.78, 
but slipped back and closed with a loss. Broad market indexes made 
substantial gains as well today, indicating a perhaps more durable 
advance in the market. The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index 
rose 33.99 to 2,462.96. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
