<HEADLINE> 2 Die in Tenn. Law Office Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- A gunman apparently upset over a  
legal matter entered his attorney's office Thursday and fatally 
shot the longtime Johnson City lawyer and a client. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said Walter V. Shell entered the law office of John D.  
Goodin about 3:30 p.m. and shot the lawyer in the head. Goodin, 81, 
died a short time later at a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	The client, 35-year-old Paul S. Keyser III, was shot in the  
chest and killed instantly. A secretary in the building was not 
hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	Shell apparently was upset over one of his relative's estate  
settlements being handled by Goodin, police Chief Ron Street said. 
He did not elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
	Shell was charged with two counts of first-degree murder and was  
being held without bond. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodin, a decorated World War II veteran, opened his law firm in  
Johnson City in 1939. He was a city judge from 1980-85 and was a 
past president of the Washington County Bar Association. He 
specialized in probate cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
