<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest Airlines Spurs Fare Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Consumers may get a break on travel through early  
August even though leisure fares have increased by as much as 7 
percent this year. 
</P>
<P>
	Major airlines quickly lowered fares on competing routes  
Thursday to match a sale announced in the morning by Southwest 
Airlines. 
</P>
<P>
	``This may be one of the last few great fare sales that we will  
see for the spring and summer travel seasons,'' said Tom Parsons, 
editor of Bestfares.com. 
</P>
<P>
	Some examples of prices for seven-day advance roundtrip fares  
included $99 between Baltimore and Fort Lauderdale, Fla., and $198 
for flights between Los Angeles and Nashville, Tenn. or Austin, 
Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	The previous best fare at American Airlines on the Austin-Los  
Angeles flight was $290, according to spokesman Tim Smith. 
</P>
<P>
	The special fares are available for purchase through April 27  
for flights until Aug. 4. Tickets are nonrefundable, must be 
purchased at least seven days in advance, and require a roundtrip 
purchase and an overnight stay. 
</P>
<P>
	Even with all the requirements, the fares are worth it, said  
Parsons, who tracks ticket prices for his Web site. 
</P>
<P>
	``What's good about this fare sale is Southwest is giving us  
almost a whole month to get our act together. This will be a great 
week to sit down and review your vacation time and talk to human 
resources about getting some time off,'' Parson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas-based Southwest has offered similar sales a few times  
each year in the past. Still, this one is unlikely to fill all of 
the seats that are expected to go empty because of overcapacity at 
several major airlines this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``It certainly helps but its not enough to offset it,'' said  
Susan Donofrio, an analyst with BT Alex. Brown. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990318.0308 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-18 00:52:52 </DATE_TIME>
