<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Life Publisher Moving to Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Ed McCarrick, the publisher of Life magazine  
since 1993, has moved to the publisher's post at sister magazine 
Time. 
</P>
<P>
	McCarrick replaces Jack Haire, who was named president of  
Fortune and Your Company magazines last month, parent company Time 
Inc. announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	McCarrick, 49, has held various positions with Time Inc. for 25  
years, beginning as a sales trainee at Time magazine in 1973. He 
was Time Inc.'s Eastern regional advertising sales director before 
becoming Life's publisher six years ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Time magazine is the nation's biggest newsweekly, with a  
circulation of 4 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Life, which has a circulation of 1.6 million, has not yet chosen  
a successor for McCarrick. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
