<HEADLINE> Joe Torre Undergoes Prostate Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- New York Yankees manager Joe Torre is  
recovering from what doctors call a successful removal of his 
cancerous prostate gland earlier today. 
</P>
<P>
	The 2 1-2-hour operation was performed at Barnes-Jewish hospital  
by Dr. William Catalona. Catalona is internationally known for his 
ability to remove prostate glands without seriously damaging nerves 
around the gland. 
</P>
<P>
	Doctors say the 58-year-old Torre is expected to be hospitalized  
for three or four days. 
</P>
<P>
	Catalona said he removed the prostate gland and lymph nodes from  
Torre and that the operation went well, with minimal apparent 
damage to surrounding nerves or tissue. 
</P>
<P>
	Torre disclosed the illness last week and has taken leave from  
the team for the surgery and an undisclosed period of recovery. 
</P>
