<HEADLINE> Fla. Seizes Lung Transplant Child </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOLLY HILL, Fla. (AP) -- A 4-year-old girl who went home from the  
hospital last week after undergoing a double lung transplant has 
been taken by child-welfare agents who say her guardians were 
neglecting her medical care. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials with the Department of Children and Families refused  
Thursday to discuss specifics of Megan Jones' case, citing state 
confidentially laws. 
</P>
<P>
	Both guardians are 65 years old. One of them, Carole LaBarr,  
blasted the agency's actions. ``They came in here like the 
Gestapo,'' she said. ``It is a case of the system run amok.'' 
