	Megan was taken from the LaBarr home near Daytona Beach late  
Wednesday, just a week after returning home from the Dec. 26 
double-lung transplant operation. 
</P>
<P>
	The state maintains that Mrs. LaBarr failed to follow a complex  
list of steps outlined in Megan's medication plan. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. LaBarr and her husband, Jim, had taken care of the girl, a  
distant relative, since July 1996 when the diaper-clad 2-year-old 
weighing just 18 pounds was brought to them by the birth mother. 
They helped care for Megan at the hospital during her 10-week 
recovery after the transplant surgery. 
