<HEADLINE> Vikings, Moon Might Reunite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EDEN PRAIRIE, Minn. (AP) -- Warren Moon, once the starting  
quarterback for the Minnesota Vikings, could come back to the club 
as the backup to Randall Cunningham. 
</P>
<P>
	The Vikings haven't really started their search for a  
replacement for Brad Johnson, who was traded to the Washington 
Redskins at the end of last season. 
</P>
<P>
	But offensive coordinator Ray Sherman and head coach Dennis  
Green both include Moon in the mix. 
</P>
<P>
	``You've got to consider him,'' Sherman said. ``He knows our  
system, and he's been here. That's something we'll look into it. 
I'd be interested in him. 
</P>
<P>
	``Warren and I talk from time to time, and I think he'd be  
interested as well. We're not going to close any doors.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Moon is a friend of Vikings owner Red McCombs, dating from his  
playing days in Houston. Moon spent 1994-96 with the Vikings. He 
played the past two seasons with Seattle but was released last 
month. 
</P>
<P>
	Moon still wants to compete for a starting job somewhere, but  
his opportunities appear to be dwindling. 
</P>
